    <h2>Biography</h2>
    <p>Ramin Jabbarli is a PhD candidate in Sociology at the University of Washington. His research examines how ritual practices shape national belonging and interethnic solidarity with a comparative focus on Iran and Turkey.</p>
    <p class="muted">Languages: English (Fluent), Azerbaijani (Native), Turkish (Fluent), Persian/Farsi (Fluent)</p>
  </section>

